The paper deals with a support recovery algorithm for sparse vectors from noisy measurements. This falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of belief propagation (BP) for posterior density estimation is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the comparison of their algorithm with other popular algorithms, which is a common practice in statistical inference (cs.SI).
